item.title: Turkcell
item.description: Turkcell is the leading mobile phone operator of Turkey, based in Istanbul. The company has 34.4 million subscribers as of September 30, 2011. In 2015, the company’s number of subscribers climbed to 68.9 million, in nine countries Largest shareholder is Telia Finland Oyj with 51% ownership. It is one of the world’s biggest companies (Fortune 2000) list published by Fortune. Source

item.title: Beko
item.description: Beko /bɛkoʊ/ (sometimes stylized as beko) is a Turkish domestic appliance and consumer electronics brand of Arçelik A.Ş. controlled by Koç Holding. Source Source

item.title: Turkish Airlines
item.description: Turkish Airlines (Turkish: Türk Hava Yolları) is the national flag carrier airline of Turkey. As of 2018, it operates scheduled services to 304 destinations in Europe, Asia, Africa, and the Americas, making it the largest carrier in the world by number of passenger destinations (excluding regional brands). It serves more destinations non-stop from a single airport than any other airline in the world. Source
